30/05/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The EU has requested a new package of constitutional amendments to guarantee the independence of the judiciary, according to a task list presented to the cabinet by Bridget Czarnota, head of the Bulgaria unit at the European Commission's enlargement directorate, who is making a three-day visit to the country.
Prime Minister Sergey Stanishev said the list must be co-ordinated with the cabinet's action plan to correct problems in certain areas, related to Bulgaria's scheduled EU accession in January 2007.
(Sega, Focus, Mediapool, BNT - 30/05/06;
BTA - 29/05/06)
